<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 23 at 4:54PM MDT  by NWS Pueblo</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southern Teller
County through 600 PM MDT...
At 452 PM MDT, Doppler radar was a band of mixed snow, sleet, very
small hail, and rain with occasional lightning along a line
extending from near Guffey to Cripple Creek. This activity is nearly
stationary
HAZARD...Accumulating pea size hail and slipper road conditions.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hazardous travel conditions.
Locations impacted include...
Cripple Creek and Victor.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling.</instruction>
